                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14730495" author="krummas" created="Fri, 4 Sep 2015 08:21:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/krummas/cassandra/commits/marcuse/10265&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14730914" author="yukim" created="Fri, 4 Sep 2015 14:56:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9142&quot; title=&quot;DC Local repair or -hosts should only be allowed with -full repair&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-9142&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-9142&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, incremental repair is not working as expected due to not running anti-compaction?&lt;br/&gt;
If we couldn&apos;t catch that in dtests, I think we need to fix incremental_repair dtest as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14730924" author="krummas" created="Fri, 4 Sep 2015 15:01:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have no idea how &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/blob/master/incremental_repair_test.py#L26&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;this&lt;/a&gt; is not catching it, but I&apos;ll have a look&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14730938" author="krummas" created="Fri, 4 Sep 2015 15:15:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;test was broken, fix pushed here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/krummas/cassandra-dtest/commit/cc4bc8ea14cb3563cf1613eb990673d2622cac26&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/krummas/cassandra-dtest/commit/cc4bc8ea14cb3563cf1613eb990673d2622cac26&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14730961" author="krummas" created="Fri, 4 Sep 2015 15:32:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;also filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10268&quot; title=&quot;Improve incremental repair tests&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10268&quot;&gt;CASSANDRA-10268&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14731037" author="yukim" created="Fri, 4 Sep 2015 16:36:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch LGTM with the fixed dtest.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For NEWS.txt, I think it&apos;d be better to change &quot;now default&quot; to &quot;default since 2.2.0&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14733286" author="krummas" created="Mon, 7 Sep 2015 06:22:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed and dtest merged, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
